<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Saibho Wu</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I submitted this to the Developers Corner on EQ, but not like I have ever seen a post that they didn't feel they could answer.<P>So I wondered, since I am not a cleric, how do you feel about this? Perhaps you can answer me?<P><BR>It is in regard to the recent cleric epic changes.<P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>You know I understand why you have done this. Malacious players.<P>What I don't understand is your resistance to letting Cleric epics into the game?<P>You say its a powerful epic?<P>Its not, the monk epic is a powerful epic, the Rogue epic is a powerful epic. These epics allow you to kill the mobs that need to be killed (pre sleepers/NToV enabled guilds, which have an abundance of epic clerics anyway and are surely not your concern?)<P>The cleric epic only cuts down on the amount of down time a raid spends after a failed attempt, and allows a cleric to rez passerbys without depleting their mana.<P>This is hardly in my mind either earth shattering or game unbalancing. Personally if you feel that 96% rezzes being given out by pre 56 level clerics is wrong, then limit the cleric epic to working only at level 55, that is well within your coding ability.<P>I would just really like to know why you feel the need to limit this epic entering the game? it gives a raid no more chance of killing a mob then they would without it. It merely cuts down the amount of time they have to spend getting back up after being knocked down.<P>Considering the amount of effort you have put into cutting down 'downtime' at the moment, Flowing Thought items, AAXP skills to increase mana regen, New and improved Clarity line, AoE Mana regen Bard songs, new spells of exactly the same merit as older spells but lasting longer, I don't understand your continued resistance to this lessening of downtime.<P>I am not saying make the cleric Epic any easier, I know and have helped several clerics from start to finish with their epic, its no easier then any other right now, but just make ragefire a spawn like some other epic mobs, once a Day EQ time, or in the case of the monk epic, every few hours.<P>Or atleast explain why you feel that this epic is worth so much more in a way I and I believe most clerics can understand.<HR></BLOCKQUOTE></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Napper</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">The cleric epic is not hard in any event compared to others.<P>Warriors have Sev to camp, SK's have Llranc, Wizards have Phini and VS, etc etc. Point is most epics have a timed spawn of 3 days at least.<P>The question is the same as why first brood dragons don't spawn daily. Rarity makes us want them the more.<P>Napper<BR>High Priest Xev</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Saibho Wu</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Rogue epic spawns daily (EQ Time)<P>Monk epic spawns hourly. I believe Xenovorash can be done on a three hour turn around.<P>I am talking only from my experience, from what I have seen done, you can leave a mob up at the rogue epic and someone else can hand in the same time and get another general. From what i gathered from the raid i was on the other night.<P>Also from what I remember, do you not have the plasmatic priest to camp? I am also pretty sure thats not all there is to it.<P>Also Warrior Epic, totally changes the class, it is one of the best taunting weapons in the game, and can make or break the killing of certain key mobs. <P>SK Epic I know nothing about. In all honesty, I do not know how good it is, or even its basic stats. Or how it affects the class.<P>Wizard epic, I think any wizard will attest is fantastic for a wizard, free rune? for a wizard..nuke city.<P>Magician Epic, possibly one of the hardest in the game, also the only epic you can take to another server, if you pay for server switch, also probably the most powerful epic for any character, in the aspect of actually changing the game for them.<P>The cleric epic does not compare to these, it does not 'make or break' any fight, all it does is save on down time.<P>Tell me, what else does the Cleric epic do for a level 56+ cleric? Add a few stats of course, but does it offer you something you do not have? does it make or break any fight?<P>It does not do any of these.<P>Of course rarity makes you want it more.<P>But rarity for the sake of it is pointless.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Saibho Wu</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>The question is the same as why first brood dragons don't spawn daily<HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Actually I don't think that is particularly true.<P>These dragons drop loot, and these loots enter into the economy, even by being upgrades that allow other equipment to be sold.<P>The economy, despite my distaste for it, is something Verant try very hard to keep stable, this is the reason I think that these dragons are spawned 3-7 days apart, nothing to do I believe in keeping certain epics out of the game. Atleast I have never heard Verant openly say this, not like they have openly admitted to the bottleneck that Ragefire causes.<P>Saibho Wu<BR>Grandmaster<BR>Lanys</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Shaydim Aashmodai</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sk epic is amazing, better than the pali epic.<P>Cleric epic requires 4 groups to go royals in chardok? 3-4 groups for ixplat? Its not easy getting that together cause lets face it, theres quite a few clerics around.<P>Now I have to go see if someoen is camping rage..and of course pvp is always fun as a cleric.<P>If they didnt change it, I would be epic now. But now I get to sit in SOL B for 24 hours now and wait...and no one will wait with me cause theres no need. Thanks verant, eq = fun right?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">LilcureEoN</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">You know  honestly I don't mind that the skyfire dragon is on a long spawn timer it is a dragon and yes can drop some good loot as well as the epic item.<P><BR>But I am now in the middle 67 hours into my camp in solb and I am now affraid that I  am going to bump up against tommorow's patch before I get it.  That is ludicrous for a turn in mob.  there isn't even a fight here.  I've been trained by FG's 6 times now, killed 3 times (buffed for 3 naggy attempts as they came past the ramp, this part was fun atleast) had a friend stay up most of the time with me.  And a little under a day from now it may all be for naught (well I guess my divination is 235 now)<P>Leave the skyfire dragon the same...the solb mob HAS to change.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aerlin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">This past weekend, a cleric in my guild was lucky enough to have SF spawn whie he was there. This is the only part he needs !!<P>We assembled forces. Approximately 5 groups, most 55+ everyone else 52+ (except one 49 war). Our main tank was a 58 Pal. We got smoked. Even with 4 58= cleric to Ch chain and plenty of druids to help keep health up, it was ugly. We did manage to get him down to 30%.<P>After we were all killed a level 60 druid tried to kite him away from the bodies so we could rez and try again. Approx. 30 mins later he despawned!!!!!!!!!<P>That was very heart wrenching! I feel for everyone who has worked so hard and for such a long time to get this mob.<P>I hope some of these issues can be resolved soon. <P>Does anyone know why this dragon despawned and others don't?  Just curious if its cuz he's an epic or what.<P>Next time its 8 groups all 55+!!<P><BR>Aerlin<BR>Sad cleric<BR>Bristlebane<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aanar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well depending on tactics used, the number of cleric epics you have can make or break the raid.  The best example is for bosses with an obscene number of hit points and a strategy often called "zerg rush".  There are many variations, but it basically involves rezzing melee during a fight over and over (with sticks) to bring down the mob.  One warrior I know died 10 times to Cazic Thule this way.   Ughh.<P>You are right, for normal expected use, the cleric epic is hardly overpowering, but when considered this way, the cleric epic *is* more powerful than any other.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aean</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ahhhh yes my friends. yet one more reason I am waiting for this <A HREF="http://www.blizzard.com/wow/" TARGET=_blank>http://www.blizzard.com/wow/</A> <P>Soon I shall no longer have to deal with VI BS and enjoy long hours of carefree gaming from a company who has never let me down <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>I just wish that one time I could be in a board room meeting at verrant just so I can hear them as they come up with these ideas, and then I would berate them in the most insideous manner. stinkin bunch of turd burglers:P</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aladain</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Saibho Wu:<