 a time constraint at the end.  Asking Verant to make this easier wont work - they have the time constraint and ragefire to be a PAIN in the ass in order to "offset" the easyness of our epic.<P>What if ragefire was a 24 hour spawn every time, but bergurgle, glimblox, and chardok overking dropped their epic items one in ten times.  Would you rather have it that way, or the way it is now?<P>Aladain</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">JanSorensen</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Just to off-set the 5 group wipeout. We killed the new Rage with 11 people - mostly 60 - and it wasnt even a fight. I can still see a single good group kill him. But with his level upped the level of your crew probably matters more for resists.<P>Warrior epic - it might be good for some but its one of the first epics to be shelved when you move further. The cleric epic on the other hand is godly.<P>------------------<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4264" TARGET=_blank>Mikar of the Nexus</A><BR>High Priest of Brell<BR><A HREF="http://companions.windsofstorm.net/" TARGET=_blank>The Companions</A><BR>The Tribunal</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">electrae</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I still don't get how anyone can call the cleric epic easy.  Easy in terms of the force it takes to knock out the mobs?  Ok, I'll grant that.  <P>Easy in terms of time invested?  No.  And now a new level of horror, the additional camp added to the epic, as if camping in Lake Rathe, Sol A and Sol B weren't enough.  And the horror of adding a hugely contested mob with an even longer spawn rate.  <P>I've done two epics now.  Rogue and cleric.  Cleric just utterly sucked.  It was boring, it was frustrating.  It took me 4 months days, and weeks of camping, to complete after I got to the last stage.  Rogue epic was fun.  I got to use my rogue skill